YES! Agreed 100%. Biggest irritation in my life with regard to doing anything with Javascript is when some library talks about some miracle function, then the example is like:<p>miracleFunction() { 
  alert(&quot;It works!&quot;)
}<p>ARGH. Give me an example of what the body of miracle function should look like!

I usually do something like<p><pre><code>  var Constants = {
    valueA: function valueA() {},
    valueB: function valueB() {}
  };</code></pre>
